"a.豪华的，奢侈的 【英】 adj. 豪华的，奢侈的 (expensive and grand) 【考】 反义词：sober(节制 的) 【记】 sumpt（拿，取）+uou s→（把钱）拿出去→ 奢侈的 adj. 豪华奢侈的 【记】sum总数, ptuous－把所有的钱都花掉－奢侈的 【反】sober(adj 冷静的; 有节制的); sobriety(n 清醒; 节制)词性不符; spartan(adj 节约的); ascetic(adj 苦行的); frugal(adj 节俭的) 【记】sum + 音：多，钱多；consume 消费 + two hours 一笔钱两小时全部花完→奢侈 sumptuous (adj.)  late 15c., from Old French sumptueux or directly from Latin sumptuosus ""costly, very expensive; lavish, wasteful,"" from sumptus, past participle of sumere ""to borrow, buy, spend, eat, drink, consume, employ, take, take up,"" contraction of *sub-emere, from sub- ""under"" (see sub-) + emere ""to take, buy"" (see exempt (adj.)). Related: Sumptuously; sumptuousness."
